-- Sensata Technologies to buy Schrader in $1 bln deal
-- By Mridhula Raghavan in Bangalore
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 06:21AM EDT
-- None



Aug 18 (Reuters) - Sensors and electrical controls maker Sensata Technologies Holding NV <ST.N> said on Monday its unit would buy Schrader group of companies from private equity firm Madison Dearborn Partners LLC for an enterprise value of $1 billion.

